Story
Once upon a time, in a forest, there lived a monkey who recided on a jamun tree, which was on
the banks of river. In the same forest, the crocodile and his wife also lived. One day, the 
crocodile came to the banks of the river and rested on the bank, the kind hearted monkey offered
him some fruits. The crocodile came back the next day for more fruits as he loved them. As days
passes by, the crocodile and the monkey became very good friends. 

Crocodile shared the fruits with his wife as well. 
One day, the monkey gave fruits for crocodile's wife. She ate the fruits and loved them but was
jealous as she did not like spending time with the monkey. She told her husband,
"Fruits are so juicy, I wonder, how sweet the heart of the monkey would be. Get me the heart of
the monkey." The crocodile was not willing to kill his friend but had no choice.